Adjusting the Bin Width

Notes: binwidth is the width of the histogram ractangles. In the below case it will set it as 10 so every ractangle will be created at width of 10 at the x-axis. ### Faceting Friend Count

# What code would you add to create a facet the histogram by gender?
# Add it to the code below.
qplot(x = friend_count, data = pf, binwidth = 10) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 1000),
                     breaks = seq(0, 1000, 50)) +
  facet_wrap(~gender)
## Warning: Removed 2951 rows containing non-finite values (stat_bin).

Omitting NA Values

Notes: Instead of using the whole data(pf), we will use a subset of the data which will omit the NA values as: data = subset(pf, !is.na(gender)), this will omit the NA values in the gender column only. We can use another way as: data = na.omit(pf) this will give the subset by removing na values in any of the columns in the whole data. We will use the first one as it is safer.

qplot(x = friend_count, data = subset(pf, !is.na(gender)), binwidth = 10) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 1000),
                     breaks = seq(0, 1000, 50)) +
  facet_wrap(~gender)
## Warning: Removed 2949 rows containing non-finite values (stat_bin).

Transforming Data

Notes: install.packages(gridExtra) ***

library(gridExtra)
p1 = ggplot(aes(x = friend_count+1), data = pf) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, fill = '#5760AB') + 
  labs(x = "Friend Count")

p2 = p1 + scale_x_log10() + labs(x = "log10(Friend Count)")

p3 = p1 + scale_x_sqrt() + labs(x = "sqrt(Friend Count)")

grid.arrange(p1, p2, p3, ncol = 1)

Frequency Polygons

ggplot(aes(x = friend_count, y = ..count../sum(..count..)),
       data = subset(pf, !is.na(gender))) +
  geom_freqpoly(aes(color = gender), binwidth=10) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 1000), breaks = seq(0, 1000, 50)) +
  xlab('Friend Count') +
  ylab('Proportion of users with that friend count')

Getting Logical

Notes:

summary(pf$mobile_likes)

mobile_check_in <- NA
pf$mobile_check_in <- ifelse(pf$mobile_likes > 0, 1, 0)
pf$mobile_check_in <- factor(pf$mobile_check_in)

summary(pf$mobile_check_in)
